\fs28 \cf0 1. Testing Types for the Course Management API\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Unit Testing
\f0\b0 \
Test Case:\uc0\u8232 Verify that the function used to create a course correctly stores the course details in the course object.\
Category:\uc0\u8232 Functional Testing\

\f1\b Integration Testing
\f0\b0 \
Test Case:\uc0\u8232 Verify that the POST 
\f2\fs26 /api/courses/
\f0\fs24  API endpoint correctly inserts the course details into the database.\
Category:\uc0\u8232 Functional Testing\

\f1\b System Testing
\f0\b0 \
Test Case:\uc0\u8232 Verify the complete workflow by creating a course using the POST API and retrieving it using the GET API.\
Category:\uc0\u8232 Functional Testing\

\f1\b User Acceptance Testing (UAT)
\f0\b0 \
Test Case:\uc0\u8232 Verify that a college administrator can successfully create a new course with valid details.\
Category:\uc0\u8232 Functional Testing\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Non-Functional Testing Example\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Performance Testing\
Test whether the Course Management API can handle 100 concurrent requests and return responses within two seconds without failures.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 2. Difference Between Black-Box Testing and White-Box Testing\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Black-Box Testing is performed without any knowledge of the application\'92s source code. The tester validates whether the application behaves correctly based on inputs and outputs. It mainly focuses on functionality and is usually performed by QA Engineers.\
White-Box Testing is performed with complete knowledge of the application\'92s internal code, logic, and structure. It focuses on code coverage, conditions, loops, and execution paths. It is usually performed by Developers.\
A QA Engineer generally performs Black-Box Testing, whereas a Developer performs White-Box Testing.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa448\partightenfactor0

