\fs36 \cf0 1. Defect Lifecycle\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The defect lifecycle follows these stages:\
New\
\uc0\u8595 \
Assigned\
\uc0\u8595 \
Open\
\uc0\u8595 \
Fixed\
\uc0\u8595 \
Retest\
\uc0\u8595 \
Verified\
\uc0\u8595 \
Closed\
Rejected:\uc0\u8232 A defect is marked as Rejected when it is invalid, cannot be reproduced, or is not considered a bug.\
Deferred:\uc0\u8232 A defect is marked as Deferred when it is accepted as a valid issue but postponed to a future release due to time constraints or lower priority.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

