\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 4. Difference Between Severity and Priority\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Severity refers to the impact a defect has on the application\'92s functionality.\
Priority refers to how urgently the defect should be fixed.\
Example:\
A spelling mistake on the CEO\'92s dashboard has Low Severity because it does not affect the application\'92s functionality. However, it has High Priority because it is visible to important stakeholders and should be corrected before release.\
